Methods: We retrospectively included 2738 patients examined by polysomnography, who in addition estimated upon awakening their total sleep time, sleep onset latency and Wake after sleep onset (WASO). We computed subjective-objective mismatch by the formula (subjective e objective value)/objective value Â100; negative and positive values indicated under- and overestimation, respectively.
