Results: The PSQI global score and Components 1 (quality) and 5 (disturbance) were correlated ( p {\textless} 0.05) with actigraphy-measured wake after sleep onset. The PSQI global score and Components 1 (quality) and 7 (daytime dysfunction) were correlated with CES-D scores. PSQI Components 2 (onset latency) and 4 (efﬁciency) were not congruent with homologous actigraphy measures, while component 3 (duration) was congruent with actigraphy duration. The single-factor PSQI global score had a higher McDonald’s omega (0.705) and Cronbach’s alpha (0.702) than the two-factor or three-factor models.
